  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building youth plaintiff leadership on climate change campaigning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The full project is to support youth plaintiffs in key climate cases in the global South to lead convening of youth plaintiffs globally and to ensure that they can lead and play a central role in developing the narrative and influencing around their cases. These cases include cases that are totemic to the global youth movement on climate change (climate strikers/Fridays for the Future (FFF)) &#x2013; e.g. Kelsey Juliana case in the US, Greta Thunberg is a plaintiff in one of the cases  - and cases that are the site of key climate justice struggles and which play a key role in global climate campaign narratives.  This grant request is to cover the attendance of one of the youth plaintiffs in a groundbreaking case in Colombia to attend COP25 (United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change Conference of the Parties) as a key opportunity to commence the network building, knowledge sharing and leading for the year long project building up to COP26. There will be immediate impact from the interventions they make also. They will speak at 2 official side events and 2 full day conferences held during COP, they will be met by Canadian youth plaintiffs who are experienced delegation at COPs as well as Pacific youth activists who are building a legal intervention, they will speak at a press conference organised by climate litigation groups globally and build up a set of actions for follow up on extending their global reach in terms of leadership and sharing the potential of their case to be replicated in other jurisdictions.</narrative>
  </description>
